A new student representative council (SRC) executive could not be sworn in at Walter Sisulu University s Buffalo City campus yesterday after a stalemate regarding the allocation of seats. Late yesterday three student organisations the South African Student Congress, PanAfricanist Student Movement of Azania (Pasma) and the Student Christian Organisation (SCO) were expected to meet in order to find a way forward.The Daily Dispatch learnt that the new SRC has yet to be constituted following SRC elections last week.Read more in today&#8217;s paper